Author: Lumbi#8378
Content:
The japanese central bank owns the overwhelming majority of their stock market. They've been propping it up for over a decade and it's actually to the point where there are almost no private investors in japanese equities anymore.

Of course, the same is true for every developed nation and most emerging market nations as well, they're just not as far along in the metamorphosis to economic collapse as Japan. The Fed balance sheet in the US is absolutely atrocious, they're holding trillions in assets to prop up the stock markets.

They keep talking about unwinding the balance sheet but they're doing it in tens of billions per month, at their current rate it would take decades to unwind and of course they're letting the air out of the bubble they inflated when they unwind it. They're just hoping they can do it slowly enough that no one catches on and there's no panic sell and that the actual fundamentals of business underlying the market will kick in and pick up the slack at some point.

They'll probably draw it out till at least the next Potus election, but eventually their strategy for hiding their extreme fiduciary irresponsibility will crash and burn.
